Sec. 147.026. RECORDING OF BOND AND STATEMENT OF SALES. (a)
The county judge shall file each commission merchant's bond with the
county clerk, who shall record the bond at length in records
maintained for that purpose labeled "Bonds of Livestock Commission
Merchants" or "Bonds of Livestock Auction Commission Merchants," as
applicable. The records must be properly indexed.
(b) If the person filing the bond is a livestock commission
merchant, the person shall also file a sworn statement with the
county judge setting forth the average daily sales of the person for
the preceding year. The county clerk shall record the statement in
the same manner as the bond.
(c) The county clerk shall file the original bond and sworn
statement of a livestock commission merchant in the clerk's office.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1381, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 1248, Sec. 23, eff. Sept. 1,
1989.

